[
    {
        "text": "ï»¿Which is the hardest word to translate in this sentence?",
        "startTime": 9233,
        "endTime": 12568,
        "slowStartTime": 14000,
        "slowEndTime": 19077
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Know\" is easy to translate.",
        "startTime": 13515,
        "endTime": 15132,
        "slowStartTime": 20422,
        "slowEndTime": 22923
    },
    {
        "text": "\"Pep rally\" doesn't have a direct analog in a lot of languages and cultures,...",
        "startTime": 15496,
        "endTime": 19555,
        "slowStartTime": 23394,
        "slowEndTime": 29558
    },
    {
        "text": "...but can be approximated.",
        "startTime": 19857,
        "endTime": 21159,
        "slowStartTime": 29936,
        "slowEndTime": 31963
    },
    {
        "text": "But the hardest word there is actually one of the smallest: \"you.\"",
        "startTime": 21659,
        "endTime": 25806,
        "slowStartTime": 32638,
        "slowEndTime": 38934
    },
    {
        "text": "As simple as it seems, it's often impossible to accurately translate \"you\"...",
        "startTime": 26487,
        "endTime": 30956,
        "slowStartTime": 39881,
        "slowEndTime": 46659
    },
    {
        "text": "...without knowing a lot more about the situation where it's being said.",
        "startTime": 31185,
        "endTime": 34803,
        "slowStartTime": 46927,
        "slowEndTime": 52429
    },
    {
        "text": "To start with, how familiar are you with the person you're talking to?",
        "startTime": 35811,
        "endTime": 40029,
        "slowStartTime": 53867,
        "slowEndTime": 60269
    },
    {
        "text": "Many cultures have different levels of formality.",
        "startTime": 40550,
        "endTime": 43525,
        "slowStartTime": 60975,
        "slowEndTime": 65512
    },
    {
        "text": "A close friend, someone much older or much younger, a stranger, a boss:...",
        "startTime": 43992,
        "endTime": 48827,
        "slowStartTime": 66138,
        "slowEndTime": 73466
    },
    {
        "text": "...these all may be slightly different yous.",
        "startTime": 49107,
        "endTime": 51838,
        "slowStartTime": 73811,
        "slowEndTime": 77982
    },
    {
        "text": "In many languages, the pronoun reflects these differences...",
        "startTime": 52890,
        "endTime": 56009,
        "slowStartTime": 79485,
        "slowEndTime": 84239
    },
    {
        "text": "...through what's known as the \"TV distinction.\"",
        "startTime": 56107,
        "endTime": 59150,
        "slowStartTime": 84311,
        "slowEndTime": 88950
    },
    {
        "text": "In French for example, you would say \"tu\" when talking to your friend at school,...",
        "startTime": 59873,
        "endTime": 64205,
        "slowStartTime": 89960,
        "slowEndTime": 96532
    },
    {
        "text": "...but \"vous\" when addressing your teacher.",
        "startTime": 64730,
        "endTime": 66635,
        "slowStartTime": 97245,
        "slowEndTime": 100178
    },
    {
        "text": "Even English once had something similar.",
        "startTime": 67329,
        "endTime": 69357,
        "slowStartTime": 101144,
        "slowEndTime": 104261
    },
    {
        "text": "Remember the old-timey \"thou?\"",
        "startTime": 69789,
        "endTime": 71611,
        "slowStartTime": 104833,
        "slowEndTime": 107642
    },
    {
        "text": "Ironically, it was actually the informal pronoun for people you're close with...",
        "startTime": 72202,
        "endTime": 76461,
        "slowStartTime": 108453,
        "slowEndTime": 114916
    },
    {
        "text": "...while \"you\" was the formal and polite version.",
        "startTime": 76736,
        "endTime": 79514,
        "slowStartTime": 115254,
        "slowEndTime": 119496
    },
    {
        "text": "That distinction was lost when the English decided to just be polite all the time.",
        "startTime": 80173,
        "endTime": 84131,
        "slowStartTime": 120409,
        "slowEndTime": 126422
    }
]